	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The reason you're receiving a hard time on this issue is because you're making a big deal out of something that happens all the time in IRC, and the fact that you're reacting to it so much (as in, you made a thread about it) just means everyone's going to give you a harder time.
<br />
<br />I understand that you may not like what others are doing, but this brings up the principles of social interaction. If you want to be social with a certain crowd, you'll likely have to adhere to their standards before they'll accept you. If you continue to assert your own preferences and try to convince others to change their ways to accomodate you, you'll just be met with more ridicule, i.e. the responses in this thread.
<br />
<br />My advice would be to just suck it up, take the extra second or two to add the apostrophe, capitalize the I, and you'll be good to go. Or, just don't give damn when someone corrects you. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
